{{Infobox scientist |name = Fritiof S. Sjöstrand |birth_date = {{birth date|1912|11|5|mf=y}} |birth_place = [[Stockholm]], [[Sweden]] |death_date = {{death date and age|2011|4|6|1912|11|5|mf=y}} |death_place = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], [[United States]] |image = Fritiof S Sjöstrand.jpg |residence = |citizenship = |nationality = |ethnicity = |fields = [[histology]] |workplaces = |alma_mater = |doctoral_advisor = |academic_advisors = |doctoral_students = |notable_students = |known_for = |author_abbrev_bot = |author_abbrev_zoo = |influences = |influenced = |awards = |religion = |signature = |footnotes = }}
'''Fritiof Stig Sjöstrand''' (November 5, 1912 – April 6, 2011)<ref>{{Cite journal | url = https://books.google.com/?id=hHlmAAAAMAAJ&q=%22Sj%C3%B6strand,+Fritiof+Stig%22+AND+%221912%22&dq=%22Sj%C3%B6strand,+Fritiof+Stig%22+AND+%221912%22 | title = Leaders in American science | year = 1963}}</ref> was a [[Sweden|Swedish]] physician and [[histology|histologist]] born in [[Stockholm]]. He started his medical education at [[Karolinska Institutet]] in 1933,<ref name="KI Bio">[http://ki.se/ki/jsp/polopoly.jsp?d=22576&l=sv Fritiof S. Sjöstrand - Biografi] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110718011200/http://ki.se/ki/jsp/polopoly.jsp?d=22576&l=sv |date=2011-07-18 }}, Karolinska Institutet 200 years {{sv icon}}</ref> where he received his Ph.D. [[Karolinska Institutet]] in 1944.<ref>Sjöstrand, Fritiof S., ''Über die Eigenfluoreszenz tierischer Gewebe mit besonderer Berücksichtigung der Säugetierniere.'', Diss. Stockholm : Karol. inst., Stockholm, 1944</ref> Sjöstrand worked as an assistant at the department of [[pharmacology]], where he first had used [[polarization microscopy]], he first heard about the new method of [[electron microscopy]] in 1938, within which he would become a pioneer. [[Manne Siegbahn]] at the Nobel Institute for Physics had planned to build an electron microscope in Sweden, and Sjöstrand got involved in the project to explore its use in medical research. The main challenge was to produce sufficiently thin samples, and Sjöstrand's method for producing ultrathin tissue samples was published in ''[[Nature (journal)|Nature]]'' in 1943.<ref name="KI Hur">[http://ki.se/ki/jsp/polopoly.jsp?d=22576&a=55947&l=sv Hur anatomiska institutionen blev internationellt centrum för elektronmikroskopi] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110718011345/http://ki.se/ki/jsp/polopoly.jsp?d=22576&a=55947&l=sv |date=2011-07-18 }}, Karolinska Institutet 200 years {{sv icon}}</ref> However, it seemed that research based on electron microscopy would be too time-consuming for a Ph.D. thesis, so his 1944 thesis was based on [[fluorescence]] spectroscopy. In 1947-1948, he received a scholarship to further study electron microscopy at [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]]'s Department of Biology. Back in Sweden, he received funding to build up an electron microscopy research laboratory. In 1959, Sjöstrand was both offered a position as professor of histology at Karolinska Institutet, and as professor at [[University of California, Los Angeles]] (UCLA). He chose UCLA, because conditions for research and funding were better there.<ref name="KI Hur"/>
Sjöstrand founded the ''[[Journal of Ultrastructure Research]]'' in 1957. Since 1990, the journal has been called the ''[[Journal of Structural Biology]]''.
Sjöstrand died on April 6, 2011, at the age of 98.
In the recognition of Fritiof Sjöstrand's contribution to the development of electron microscopy, the Annual Sjöstrand Lecture series was set up in 2018 in Sweden<ref>https://www.scilifelab.se/events/inaugural-sjostrand-lecture-in-structural-biology-by-venki-ramakrishnan/</ref>. A holder of the lectureship particularly commits to spend time with students and postdocs at [[SciLifeLab]]. The Inaugural Lecture is given by [[Venki Ramakrishnan]] on 27th August 2018 at the [[Karolinska Institute]] and entitled ’Termination of translation in bacteria and eukaryotes'. The 2019 lecture will be given by [[Jennifer Doudna]].
== References == * [https://web.archive.org/web/20120406095136/http://today.ucla.edu/portal/ut/in-memoriam--fritiof-s--sjostrand--a-star-in-electron-microscopy.aspx In Memoriam] * {{cite journal|doi=10.1016/j.jsb.2008.03.004|url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science?_ob=ArticleURL&_udi=B6WM5-4S3G3X4-1&_user=10&_coverDate=09%2F30%2F2008&_rdoc=1&_fmt=high&_orig=search&_sort=d&_docanchor=&view=c&_searchStrId=1405185190&_rerunOrigin=google&_acct=C000050221&_version=1&_urlVersion=0&_userid=10&md5=ebd52a5671267d2eb002a2ab8354626b |title=A profile of Fritiof S. Sjöstrand—The founding editor | author=Arvid B. Maunsbach |journal=Journal of Structural Biology |volume=163 |issue=3 |date=September 2008| pages=196–200 |publisher=[[Elsevier]]|pmid=18424073}} {{Reflist}}
