{{Infobox lake | name = Lago di Malciaussia | image = Malciaussia.jpg | caption = | image_bathymetry = | caption_bathymetry = | location = [[Italy]], [[Graian Alps]] | coords = {{coord|45|12|N|7|8|E|type:waterbody_region:IT|display=inline,title}} | type = | inflow = [[Stura di Viù]] | outflow = [[Stura di Viù]] | catchment = | basin_countries = [[Italy]] | length = | width = | area = | depth = | max-depth = | volume = | residence_time = | shore = | elevation = {{convert|1,805|m|abbr=on}} | frozen = | islands = | cities = }} '''Lago di Malciaussia''' is a [[reservoir]] situated at an elevation of 1,805 metres <ref name=laghi>{{cite book|title=Atlante dei laghi Piemontesi| author=Direzione Pianificazione delle Risorse Idriche |publisher= Regione Piemonte | year= 2003 }}</ref> in the upper [[Valle di Viù]] in the north-west [[Italy|Italian]] [[province of Turin]].
== History == [[File:Costruzione diga Malciaussia.jpg|thumb|Dam building]] The reservoir was constructed in the 1920s and 1930s by damming the [[Stura di Viù]], a tributary of the [[Stura di Lanzo]], for the generation of [[hydropower]]. It is named after the locality Malciaussia—a ''[[frazione]]'' of the [[comune|commune]] of [[Usseglio]]—which was submerged when it was filled.
== Hiking == The valley road terminates at this lake which makes it a convenient starting point for walking and climbing in the high [[Alps]]. From here one can ascend [[Rocciamelone]] (3,538 m), via the [[Mountain hut|alpine hut]] “Ernesto Tazzetti”. The routes to Monte Lera, Punta Costan and [[Punta Sulè]] start as well from the lake.<ref name=beru>{{cite book|last= Berutto |first= Giulio |title= Valli di Lanzo e Moncenisio |year= 1983 |publisher= Istituto Geografico Centrale |location = Torino }}</ref>
