'''Mushbooh''' ({{lang-ar|مشبوه}}) is a [[Islamic dietary laws|food designation in Islam]]. Literally meaning "doubtful" or "suspect," foods are labeled mushbooh when it is unclear whether they are ''[[Halal]]'' (consumption is permitted) or [[Haraam]]([[haram]]) (consumption is prohibited).

